    • Field Detail

      • stopNegotiation

        public boolean stopNegotiation
        stopNegotiation indicates that the session has now ended. it is checked after every call to the agent, and if it happens to be true, session is immediately returned without any updates to the results list. This is because killing the thread in many cases will return Agent.getActions() but with a stale action. By setting stopNegotiation to true before killing, the agent will still immediately return.

    • Method Detail

      • run

        public void run()
        a parent thread will call this via the Thread.run() function. Then it will start a timer to handle the time-out of the negotiation. At the end of this run, we will notify the parent so that he does not keep waiting for the time-out.

      • intercept

        protected Action intercept(Action lastAction)
                    throws java.lang.Exception
        Does not usually intercept anything, but when "oneSidedBidding" is enabled in the settings, then agent A's bids are ignored, and replaced by the bid that has max utility for A.

      • JudgeTimeout

        public void JudgeTimeout()
        This is called whenever the protocol is timed-out. What happens in case of a time-out is (1) the sessionrunner is killed with a Thread.interrupt() call from the NegotiationSession2. (2) judgeTimeout() is called.
